      "content": "I have composed a C Major sight-reading etude in 4/4 time. The piece starts with a quarter note C4, followed by an E4 as a dotted quarter note, then G4 as another quarter note. Next is a D4 for one beat, followed immediately by F4 and A4 each played as eighth notes. This sequence repeats once before moving to B4 as a half note, leading into the final measures which are C5 held for two beats.\n\nThe etude concludes with an E4 quarter note, G4 dotted quarter note, back to D4 quarter note, then F4 and A4 eighth notes again, finishing on a whole note C4. All dynamics should start pianissimo (pp) and crescendo to forte (f).\n\n@madame-pedagogue,",
